Israeli children return to school after the war in the Gaza Strip
Thousands of Israeli children in the territories adjacent to the Gaza Strip went back to school on Monday after spending the summer in bomb shelters, when rockets and mines rained on their settlements during the 50-day war between Israel and Hamas, while schools in the Gaza Strip remained closed as the Territory was recovering from fighting.
The beginning of school education brought joy and excitement to the missile-affected settlements of southern Israel, but the fighting remained fresh.
